name: Test -> lamp module load (main lamp and indicator),
description: Test the main and indicator lamps in the load module for unintended feedback or parasitic oscillation by measuring the voltage across them and inspecting for any spurious voltage or current changes in sync with the oscillation. Inspect if diode leakage or partial breakdown might be present., outcome='The main lamp and internal indicator lamp both show voltages near supply level and are drawing expected currents, with some signs of circuit instability or oscillation noted. The load protection diode appears to be operating correctly, with forward voltage matching nominal values and no evidence of leakage or breakdown in static measurements. POLARITY INVERSION was not detected in the measured voltage or component connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=145.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0), ('test_diode', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
